rdf:Description.ns1:label: Quercus cerris
rdf:Description.ns1:abstract: Quercus cerris, the Turkey oak or Austrian oak, is an oak native to south-eastern Europe and Asia Minor. It is the type species of Quercus sect. Cerris, a section of the genus characterised by shoot buds surrounded by soft bristles, bristle-tipped leaf lobes, and acorns that usually mature in 18 months.
rdf:Description.ns1:zone: Zona 4 - Sectia Flora si Vegetatia Romaniei
